---
/**
 * Fula Devi. Who she was, shown through what she actually did.
 * The person, not the institution — the institution appears only because it
 * continues her example. Philosophy belongs on The Institution page.
 */
import ContentPage from '../layouts/ContentPage.astro';
import Quote from '../components/Quote.astro';
---

<ContentPage
  title="Fula Devi"
  description="Who Fula Devi was, the quiet ways she helped others, the dignity she preserved, and the teaching remembered by her family."
>
  <p>Fula Devi never founded an institution.</p>
  <p>
    She lived an ordinary life and quietly helped people whenever she could.
  </p>
  <p>She never sought recognition for those acts.</p>
  <p>
    The institution that bears her name exists because those quiet acts of
    kindness deserved continuity.
  </p>

  <h2>She Helped Quietly</h2>
  <p>Helping others was part of her everyday life.</p>
  <p>
    She did what she could, whenever she could, without expecting recognition.
  </p>

  <h2>She Preserved Dignity</h2>
  <p>Anyone who came to work at her home was first offered food.</p>
  <p>Helping someone should never make that person feel smaller.</p>
  <p>Dignity mattered as much as the help itself.</p>

  <h2>She Helped Without Judgement</h2>
  <p>She quietly helped people whom others often ignored.</p>
  <p>
    A person's circumstances never determined whether they deserved kindness.
  </p>

  <h2>She Encouraged Independence</h2>
  <p>
    She encouraged her daughters to become educated and financially
    independent, even when doing so challenged social expectations.
  </p>

  <h2>She Respected Every Faith</h2>
  <p>
    Although deeply devoted to her own faith, she respected every sincere
    search for the Divine.
  </p>
  <p>
    She once sent her son to a mosque because she believed respect should never
    stop at religious boundaries.
  </p>

  <h2>A Teaching Remembered</h2>
  <p>One teaching remained with her family.</p>
  <Quote>
    Don't chant.<br />
    Don't perform rituals.<br />
    Search for the Divine within yourself.<br />
    Serve the living.<br />
    Feed others.<br />
    Give water to a cow.<br />
    That is worship.<br />
    That is truth.
  </Quote>
</ContentPage>
